comments.body:
@patbaumgartner those are two different things. Petclinic should not build with Java < 22 due to compiler bugs that haven't been backported. Building with Java 17 should not be possible and I'll revisit this shortly. 

The JDK you use to build the project and the JVM you use to run the application are two different things. As you know, Spring Bot has nullability support. You need Java 22+ to build the project, but you can obviously run Spring Boot apps on 17.

Going forward, I think it'd be beneficial to have more focused changes. This PR in particular is interesting as it can be used as an educational material for folks wondering what it takes to upgrade to SB 4. The unrelated changes in this PR (like the upgrade of versions) adds noise. They are very useful of course, but a separate PR that focuses only on that would have been better in my opinion.
